						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Koyil-Kulaśēkharadēva, 2nd year = c. 13th-14th Century.</p>						

						<p>Miḻichchār <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Piḷḷai Pallavarāyar purchased land from the ūrār of Kūḻaikuḷattūr in Kīḷ-Koṉāḍu and gave it as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> to the temple of Sundirachōḻīśvaram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār in the same village for conducting a service called Pallavan-<hi rend="italic">sandi</hi> in his name.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 555.]</p>						

						</summary>
